paragraphs.text:
%md

On initial query, the system takes around 22 seconds to do a count of rows. The system then caches the data grabbed, resulting in 15 seconds beig taken for a re-run of the query. Erasure of the caches using the following command:
```bash
echo 3 | sudo tee /proc/sys/vm/drop_caches
```
on the worker nodes had query back to taking around 20+ seconds to execute.

Let's find out the highest GDP growth for each country.

Highest GDP growth ever for all countries

Let’s find out the highest GDP growth for each country.

paragraphs.text:
-- Querying using the columnar table
SELECT main.indicatorvalue, main.year, main.countryname
FROM wdi_csv_parquet main
INNER JOIN
(
    SELECT MAX(indicatorvalue) as GDP_growth_value, countryName FROM wdi_csv_parquet WHERE indicatorcode LIKE "NY.GDP.MKTP.KD.ZG" 
GROUP BY countryname 
) subs
ON main.indicatorvalue = subs.GDP_growth_value and main.countryname = subs.countryname
ORDER BY main.indicatorvalue DESC

SELECT main.indicatorvalue, main.year, main.countryname
FROM wdi_csv_parquet main
INNER JOIN
(
    SELECT MAX(indicatorvalue) as GDP_growth_value, countryName FROM wdi_csv_parquet WHERE indicatorcode LIKE "NY.GDP.MKTP.KD.ZG" 
GROUP BY countryname 
) subs
ON main.indicatorvalue = subs.GDP_growth_value and main.countryname = subs.countryname
ORDER BY main.indicatorvalue DESC
